00:53:19,428 --> 00:53:22,358
look what happened because of you two.

776
00:53:23,268 --> 00:53:25,628
We had to quit shooting yesterday

777
00:53:26,428 --> 00:53:28,298
and we're about to quit today, too.

778
00:53:28,298 --> 00:53:30,098
That's because...

779
00:53:30,098 --> 00:53:34,848
Dozens of staff members prepared for the shoot since dawn,

780
00:53:34,848 --> 00:53:37,008
but because of the two of you...

781
00:53:37,988 --> 00:53:41,088
This isn't right.

782
00:53:45,748 --> 00:53:50,648
And I'm not trying to defend Mr. Cha at all.

783
00:53:50,648 --> 00:53:54,068
I was at the team outing then, too.

784
00:53:54,068 --> 00:53:59,988
Your behavior definitely was misleading.

785
00:54:00,878 --> 00:54:04,468
If that's what caused the misunderstanding,

786
00:54:04,468 --> 00:54:08,178
I think it's important to straighten things out.

787
00:54:12,028 --> 00:54:13,768
Ms. Park,

788
00:54:15,078 --> 00:54:20,108
countless people's fates depend on "Straightforward Romance."

789
00:54:20,108 --> 00:54:23,668
For the countless staff members

790
00:54:23,668 --> 00:54:27,218
and the viewers who are looking forward to it,

791
00:54:27,218 --> 00:54:33,348
could you make up with Mr. Cha today and get back to shooting?

792
00:54:35,058 --> 00:54:36,828
I beg you.

793
00:54:48,088 --> 00:54:49,948
Okay.

794
00:54:51,318 --> 00:54:56,738
Thinking about it, I think I was wrong, too.

795
00:54:56,738 --> 00:55:01,028
I'll apologize to Bong Soo.

796
00:55:01,028 --> 00:55:03,598
R-Really?

797
00:55:03,598 --> 00:55:07,278
But he keeps swearing at me...

798
00:55:07,278 --> 00:55:10,838
and tries to hit me and start a fight.

799
00:55:10,838 --> 00:55:16,768
I'd like you to come with me when I apologize to him.

800
00:55:16,768 --> 00:55:19,468
Of course, I will.

801
00:55:19,468 --> 00:55:21,228
Thank you.

802
00:55:24,008 --> 00:55:25,838
So spicy.

803
00:55:33,028 --> 00:55:34,908
What?

804
00:55:34,908 --> 00:55:36,608
Are you here to slap me again?

805
00:55:36,608 --> 00:55:37,948
No.

806
00:55:37,948 --> 00:55:44,758
Ms. Park is here to apologize to you, Mr. Cha.

807
00:55:46,188 --> 00:55:47,798
What did you say?

808
00:55:47,798 --> 00:55:53,078
Oppa, I'm so sorry for slapping you.

809
00:55:53,688 --> 00:55:57,408
I did it in the heat of the moment, but...

810
00:55:58,818 --> 00:56:01,428
I sincerely apologize.

811
00:56:02,968 --> 00:56:07,418
And I did mislead you, too.

812
00:56:07,418 --> 00:56:10,528
I drank too much that night.

813
00:56:10,528 --> 00:56:14,408
I must've found you handsome because I was so drunk.

814
00:56:14,408 --> 00:56:18,348
I did confuse you by saying silly things.

815
00:56:19,588 --> 00:56:24,438
But that was it. Nothing happened between us, right?

816
00:56:24,438 --> 00:56:27,248
I know I don't get along with Bi Bi,

817
00:56:27,248 --> 00:56:29,688
but we've been colleagues for a long time.

818
00:56:29,688 --> 00:56:33,658
It shouldn't have happened even if I liked you.

819
00:56:33,658 --> 00:56:35,578
Anyway,

820
00:56:37,148 --> 00:56:40,968
I'm sorry for misleading you.

821
00:56:40,968 --> 00:56:42,988
It's my fault.

822
00:56:44,378 --> 00:56:46,278
I apologize.

823
00:56:51,158 --> 00:56:53,710
I'm sorry for swearing...

824
00:56:54,298 --> 00:56:56,038
at you, too.

825
00:56:57,048 --> 00:57:01,208
Of course. This is why you're big-name actors.

826
00:57:01,208 --> 00:57:05,578
You generously apologized... and you accepted the apology generously, too.

827
00:57:05,578 --> 00:57:08,608
Is this why you're big-name actors?

828
00:57:10,208 --> 00:57:13,488
We'll take a break for an hour and resume shooting.

829
00:57:13,488 --> 00:57:15,158
Let's go!

830
00:57:15,858 --> 00:57:17,838
Let's go!

831
00:57:25,358 --> 00:57:27,398
Thank you.

832
00:57:34,528 --> 00:57:36,978
You said you wanted to tell me something.

833
00:57:36,978 --> 00:57:39,608
What is it that makes you so hesitant?

834
00:57:39,608 --> 00:57:43,598
I get scared whenever you say you need to talk to me.

835
00:57:43,598 --> 00:57:49,258
Well, you know Myeong Soo, right? My high school classmate.

836
00:57:50,298 --> 00:57:52,268
What about him?

837
00:57:52,268 --> 00:57:56,538
By chance, you aren't saying you'll start a business, right?

838
00:57:56,538 --> 00:58:03,198
Apparently, used Korean phones are in huge demand in Vietnam.

839
00:58:03,198 --> 00:58:05,128
They sell like hotcakes.

840
00:58:05,128 --> 00:58:08,348
So, Myeong Soo figured out how to start the business.

841
00:58:08,348 --> 00:58:11,668
He said this would be a piece of cake.

842
00:58:11,668 --> 00:58:13,558
So...

843
00:58:14,488 --> 00:58:20,258
why don't we borrow 200 million with this house as collateral?

844
00:58:20,258 --> 00:58:23,298
What are you talking about right now?

845
00:58:23,298 --> 00:58:28,198
You borrowed 300 million with this house as collateral to start a business, but it totally failed.

846
00:58:28,198 --> 00:58:33,458
Pil Sung is paying back the loan amount and interest right now.

847
00:58:33,458 --> 00:58:36,378
Don't you feel bad for Pil Sung at all?

848
00:58:36,378 --> 00:58:39,158
How could you bring up getting a loan again?

849
00:58:39,158 --> 00:58:42,948
That's why I'm trying to succeed and pay him back.

850
00:58:42,948 --> 00:58:44,538
Please help me just once more.

851
00:58:44,538 --> 00:58:46,678
This one's guaranteed. I'm telling you.

852
00:58:46,678 --> 00:58:49,408
Honey, please don't do this.

853
00:58:49,408 --> 00:58:52,458
I don't want anything from you.

854
00:58:52,458 --> 00:58:57,348
Just don't do anything and sit still. Please.

855
00:58:57,348 --> 00:58:58,958
Hey.

856
00:58:59,858 --> 00:59:03,748
Seon Yeong, how could you be like this?

857
00:59:03,748 --> 00:59:08,188
You should help wholeheartedly if the head of the household wants to do something.

858
00:59:08,188 --> 00:59:10,628
But what? What did you say just now?

859
00:59:10,628 --> 00:59:14,688
Don't do anything and just stay in the room?

860
00:59:14,688 --> 00:59:18,428
Is Hyeon Cheol a dead man? Why would he stay in the room?

861
00:59:19,648 --> 00:59:23,368
Mother, this house is all we have.

862
00:59:23,368 --> 00:59:27,188
We'd be out in the streets if we lost this, too.

863
00:59:27,188 --> 00:59:30,678
Hey! You're acting superior because of this house,

864
00:59:30,678 --> 00:59:34,698
but before Hyeon Cheol got fired from his job five years ago,

865
00:59:34,698 --> 00:59:39,488
he's been feeding everyone in the family as the head of the household.

866
00:59:39,488 --> 00:59:43,628
Your father bought this house under your name,

867
00:59:43,628 --> 00:59:46,778
but Hyeon Cheol owns half of it, too.

868
00:59:46,778 --> 00:59:51,148
How could you act so superior for owning a house?

869
00:59:51,148 --> 00:59:55,618
Mother, when did I act superior because of the house?

870
00:59:55,618 --> 00:59:58,858
It's because we need to protect this house, at least.

871
00:59:58,858 --> 01:00:01,898
I'm saying this because we're on the topic.

872
01:00:01,898 --> 01:00:07,738
I'm sorry to say this since he has passed, but I'm so disappointed in your father.

873
01:00:07,738 --> 01:00:11,668
He let his son-in-law feed him while he was alive,

874
01:00:11,668 --> 01:00:17,158
but how could he only put your name on the deed?

875
01:00:17,158 --> 01:00:22,208
He had no problem giving that gold digger 30 million won!

876
01:00:22,208 --> 01:00:26,528
Mom, why would you say that?

877
01:00:26,528 --> 01:00:30,398
- Geez. 
 - Hey, Hyeon Cheol... Hyeon Cheol.

878
01:00:30,398 --> 01:00:33,778
Hyeon Cheol. Hyeon Cheol. Hyeon Cheol!

879
01:00:33,778 --> 01:00:35,818
 Hyeon Cheol! 

880
01:00:38,888 --> 01:00:40,858
 Hyeon Cheol! 

881
01:00:51,958 --> 01:00:54,328
My poor Hyeon Cheol.

882
01:00:55,658 --> 01:01:01,638
He's so intimidated by his wife because of his pathetic parents.

883
01:01:18,178 --> 01:01:24,158
Yes. I need to get that money back, at least.

884
01:01:37,158 --> 01:01:39,698
Is this the right place?

885
01:01:45,268 --> 01:01:48,348
Yes, this is it.

886
01:01:53,108 --> 01:01:55,408
Hey, Ms. Baek.

887
01:02:01,998 --> 01:02:04,258
Why are you so surprised?

888
01:02:04,878 --> 01:02:07,568
Did you see a ghost or something?

889
01:02:11,288 --> 01:02:14,408
I really don't want to do the kiss scene.

890
01:02:14,408 --> 01:02:17,428
Gosh, what do we do?

891
01:02:17,428 --> 01:02:19,148
Should I do it in your place?

892
01:02:19,148 --> 01:02:21,058
Would you?

893
01:02:24,528 --> 01:02:26,758
Have some.

894
01:02:27,608 --> 01:02:29,528
Assistant Director.

895
01:02:30,798 --> 01:02:32,528
What's this?

896
01:02:32,528 --> 01:02:35,658
How did you know I was craving ice cream?

897
01:02:36,548 --> 01:02:41,018
You apologized to Mr. Cha for our drama and you finished the difficult scene in one go.

898
01:02:41,018 --> 01:02:44,968
So I wanted to thank you for that.

899
01:02:44,968 --> 01:02:49,418
I read that you eat ice cream whenever you feel down.

900
01:02:49,418 --> 01:02:51,688
I wanted to cheer you up.

901
01:02:51,688 --> 01:02:53,868
My gosh.

902
01:02:54,688 --> 01:02:58,888
I... I'm so moved right now.

903
01:02:59,778 --> 01:03:01,778
That's nothing.

904
01:03:01,778 --> 01:03:04,328
I'll get going now, then.

905
01:03:07,008 --> 01:03:12,028
Excuse me. Assistant Director Go Pil Sung,

906
01:03:12,028 --> 01:03:15,618
thank you for everything.

907
01:03:15,618 --> 01:03:18,558
Gosh, it's nothing.

908
01:03:18,558 --> 01:03:21,918
You've been helping and saving me.

909
01:03:21,918 --> 01:03:25,268
At the club, when Bi Bi flipped out,

910
01:03:25,268 --> 01:03:27,888
and when I almost got hit by Bong Soo.

911
01:03:27,888 --> 01:03:34,888
Because my duty is to protect the female lead in our drama.

912
01:03:34,888 --> 01:03:39,178
I'll work hard on this project to return the favor to you.

913
01:03:39,178 --> 01:03:41,328
So don't worry.

914
01:03:41,328 --> 01:03:44,498
I won't give you a hard time.

915
01:03:45,498 --> 01:03:49,708
Thank you so much. I'll work hard, too.

916
01:03:57,038 --> 01:03:58,848
 It's okay. 

917
01:03:58,848 --> 01:04:01,268
 I have a lot of hair. 

918
01:04:02,308 --> 01:04:04,098
Oh, right.

919
01:04:04,098 --> 01:04:08,228
Dae Chung Oppa said that a long time ago.

920
01:04:13,308 --> 01:04:16,388
I wonder if Dae Chung Oppa is doing well.

921
01:04:16,388 --> 01:04:18,448
I wonder what he's up to.

922
01:04:19,978 --> 01:04:23,318
Ms. Park, get ready for the next scene.

923
01:04:25,358 --> 01:04:28,498
Gosh, how strange.

924
01:04:28,498 --> 01:04:32,748
Why does the curly-haired director remind me of Dae Chung Oppa?

925
01:04:37,558 --> 01:04:42,838
Is it because his hair looks just like Dae Chung Oppa's?

926
01:04:44,158 --> 01:04:45,858
Hold on.

927
01:04:45,858 --> 01:04:48,268
Go Dae Chung.

928
01:04:48,268 --> 01:04:50,188
Go Pil Sung.

929
01:04:51,188 --> 01:04:54,108
What? Even his last name is Go, too.

930
01:04:54,108 --> 01:04:56,880
We'll start shooting! Stand by!

931
